    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics - Circuit Diagnostics - CAN
        (Controller Area Network) Communications
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010706.7" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CAN (Controller Area Network) Communications</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010706.7.1">
            <figure id="f305010734" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31074.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>Function diagram for CAN</caption>
            </figure>
            <para id="s305010706.7.1.1"></para>
            <table id="t305010756" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The function diagram for the CAN includes the following:</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Electronic Control Module (ECM)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Drivetrain Datalink (CAN1)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Terminating resistors - 120-ohm</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Instrument Panel (Lamps)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Other nodes</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Function</title>The Drivetrain Datalink is a Society of Automotive Engineers (SAE) term referring
                to datalinks common to trucks. The Drivetrain Datalink is the communication link for the Electronic
                Control Module (ECM), cab and chassis, instrument panel, and is also used for power train communication
                and control.
            </para>
            <para>The ECM transmits component information across the Drivetrain Datalink to the instrument panel.</para>
            <table id="t305010757" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>The following instrument panel components are in constant communication with the Drivetrain
                    Datalink:
                </title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Tachometer</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Speedometer</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Odometer</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Coolant temperature gauge</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Red Lamp (Oil/Water Lamp (OWL) for CF)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Amber Lamp (Warn Engine Lamp (WEL) for CF)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Change oil lamp</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>WAIT TO START lamp</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Water In Fuel (WIF) lamp</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Anti-lock Breaking System (ABS)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>
                <title>Fault Detection/Management</title>There are no engine DTCs for CAN1 communications.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>See the applicable truck Circuit Diagram Manual and Service Manual.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t305010758" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Tools</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.0*"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EST with MasterDiagnostics&#174; software</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>EZ-Tech&#174; interface cable</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>DMM</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010706.7.2">
            <title>CAN Pin-Point Diagnostics</title>
            <figure id="f305010735" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj31/J31075.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"/>
                <caption>CAN communication circuit diagram</caption>
            </figure>
            <table id="t305010759" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Voltage Checks</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Check at EST connector with key-on engine-off.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0" align="center">
                                <para>Signal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>B to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>B+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>Power</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>Should be B+ power at B all times. If no power, check ground and power circuits.
                                    See the applicable truck Circuit Diagram Manual.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>C to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 to 4 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Digital signal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The sum of C to A and D to A equals 4 to 5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>D to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1 to 4 V</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Digital signal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The sum of C to A and D to A equals 4 to 5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t305010760" tblwidth="pg-wide" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Resistance Checks</title>
                <tgroup cols="4">
                    <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="COLSPEC0" colwidth="0.86in"/>
                    <colspec colname="col3" colwidth="3.00*"/>
                    <spanspec namest="col1" nameend="col3" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <warning>
                                    <para>To avoid personal injury, death, including damage to the engine or vehicle,
                                        always disconnect main negative battery cable first. Always connect the main
                                        negative battery cable last.
                                    </para>
                                </warning>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="4" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>Turn ignition switch to OFF. Check at EST connector with negative battery cable
                                    disconnected.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1" align="center">
                                <para>Test Point</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2" align="center">
                                <para>Spec</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0" align="center">
                                <para>Signal</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3" align="center">
                                <para>Comments</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>C to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>1 M&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>CAN+</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If less than 1 M&#x2126;, a short between CAN+ and ground exists. Disconnect ECM
                                    X3 and check again. If short is no longer present, replace ECM. If short exists,
                                    harness or other node component failure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>D to A</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>1 M&#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>CAN-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>If less than 1 M&#x2126;, a short between CAN- and ground exists. Disconnect ECM
                                    X3 and check again. If short is no longer present, replace ECM. If short still
                                    exists, harness or other node component failure.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="col1">
                                <para>C to D</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col2">
                                <para>60 &#x2126;</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="COLSPEC0">
                                <para>CAN</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="col3">
                                <para>The datalink has two terminating resistors in parallel of 120 &#x2126; each. If
                                    greater than 70 &#x2126;, check for missing terminating resister or open in the CAN+
                                    or CAN- wires. If less than 50 &#x2126;, check for extra terminating resistor. If
                                    less than 5 &#x2126;, check for short between CAN+ and CAN-.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
